'''Mohanad Ali Kadhim Al-Shammari''' ({{langx|ar|مُهَنَّد عَلِيّ كَاظِم الشَّمَّرِيّ}}, born 20 June 2000), commonly known in Iraq as '''Mimi''' ({{langx|ar|ميمي}}), is an Iraqi professional [[Forward (association football)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for UAE club [[Dibba FC|Dibba]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]]. He is known for his positioning, shooting, heading, close ball control and dribbling.<ref name="it" >{{cite web|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/il-talento-del-giorno/i-un-talento-al-giorno-i-mohanad-ali-il-primo-iracheno-bianconero-1218546|title=Un talento al giorno, Mohanad Ali: il primo iracheno bianconero?|first=Simone|last=Lorini|publisher=Tuttomercatoweb.com|date=27 February 2019|language=it|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329110947/https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/il-talento-del-giorno/i-un-talento-al-giorno-i-mohanad-ali-il-primo-iracheno-bianconero-1218546|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Top 10 forwards to watch out for|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/afc-asian-cup-2019-top-10-forwards-to-watch-out-for|publisher=Sportskeeda|date=22 December 2018|access-date=24 December 2018|archive-date=23 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181223052341/https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/afc-asian-cup-2019-top-10-forwards-to-watch-out-for|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Mohanad Ali – Forvet|work=Genç Scout|url=http://www.gencscout.com/2019/01/27/mohanad-ali-kadhim-18-forvet-santrafor-al-shorta-sc/|date=27 January 2019|language=tr|access-date=30 January 2019|archive-date=27 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327161322/http://www.gencscout.com/2019/01/27/mohanad-ali-kadhim-18-forvet-santrafor-al-shorta-sc/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Youth career===
Ali became interested in football as a child and started playing for a local team in the [[New Baghdad|Baghdad Al-Jadida]] district called ''Timsah Al-Amin''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Facts on Mohanad Ali|url=https://twitter.com/hassaninmubarak/status/1084432570945859584|access-date=15 January 2019|archive-date=27 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327054154/https://twitter.com/hassaninmubarak/status/1084432570945859584|url-status=live}}</ref> He enrolled at the [[Ammo Baba|Ammo Baba Football School]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad enrolled at the age of six|url=https://twitter.com/hassaninmubarak/status/964629267245158401|access-date=4 July 2018|archive-date=27 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327054152/https://twitter.com/hassaninmubarak/status/964629267245158401|url-status=live}}</ref> at the age of six without a trial after coaches had been impressed with the striker. He then joined the [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] youth team,<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad Ali with Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya in 2012–2013 season|website=[[Facebook]]|url=https://www.facebook.com/jawiyak/posts/825289994483289|access-date=9 February 2020|archive-date=22 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022122336/https://www.facebook.com/jawiyak/posts/825289994483289|url-status=live}}</ref> and he represented them in the Al-Zawraa Youth Championship;<ref>{{cite web|title=Rawan Al-Nahi report on Mohanad Ali|url=https://forum.kooora.com/f.aspx?t=34820458|access-date=9 February 2020|archive-date=31 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211231150750/https://forum.kooora.com/f.aspx?t=34820458|url-status=live}}</ref> he was top scorer at two local tournaments, and was then called up by the [[Iraq Football Association|Iraq FA]] to play for Saad Hashim's under-14 team, and with an outstanding performance,<ref name="Hurra" >{{cite web|title=Al-Hurra Iraq tv report on Mohanad Ali|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CXI5StgLMHg|date=30 August 2013|publisher=[[Alhurra]]|access-date=19 December 2017|archive-date=23 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323153333/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CXI5StgLMHg|url-status=live}}</ref> he grabbed the attention of the managers of [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]].<ref name="SHC" >{{cite web|title=He signed a five-year contract with Al-Shorta|url=https://forum.kooora.com/f.aspx?t=33312897|date=24 September 2013|access-date=26 October 2020|archive-date=27 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727100256/https://forum.kooora.com/f.aspx?t=33312897|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Al-Shorta===
====Early years====
On 24 September 2013, Ali signed a five-year contract with [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]] and took the number 26 shirt.<ref name="SHC" /> He became the youngest player in [[Iraqi Premier League]] history at 13 years and 279 days old when he made his competitive debut for Al-Shorta under Brazilian coach [[Lorival Santos]] in the [[2013–14 Iraqi Premier League]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Al-Talaba 1–2 Al-Shorta Full Match|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FcHBaDvd4-A&t=5413|access-date=13 January 2019|archive-date=27 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727100255/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FcHBaDvd4-A&t=5413|url-status=live}}</ref> being substituted onto the field on 85 minutes in the [[Baghdad Derbies|Baghdad Derby]] against [[Al-Talaba]] on 26 March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Al-Shorta SC: Overview of History|url=https://alshorta.webs.com/overview-of-history|access-date=13 January 2019|archive-date=4 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221004102515/https://alshorta.webs.com/overview-of-history|url-status=live}}</ref> Al-Shorta topped the league standings with 43 points from 21 games, although the league was ended prematurely due to the war situation in the country.<ref name="title">{{cite web|title=Al-Shorta SC: Latest News|url=https://alshorta.webs.com/latest-news|access-date=16 April 2019|archive-date=14 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814025715/https://alshorta.webs.com/latest-news|url-status=live}}</ref>

In the [[2014–15 Al-Shorta SC season|2014–15]] season, Mohanad played in a four-team friendly competition called the [[Tournament for the Armed Forces]], scoring a penalty in the semi-final shootout which Al-Shorta lost to [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Penalty Kicks between Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya and Al-Shorta|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=48rLlTkIHvY&t=100|access-date=30 December 2018|archive-date=23 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323153337/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=48rLlTkIHvY&t=100|url-status=live}}</ref>
Mohanad was given the number 8 shirt for the [[2015–16 Al-Shorta SC season|2015–16]] season under coach [[Hakeem Shaker]] and he scored his first goal for Al-Shorta on 20 September 2015 against [[Al-Sinaa SC|Al-Sinaa]] in the [[2015–16 Iraqi Premier League]] with a header.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad scored his first goal for Al-Shorta|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N_MNMZV9dTY&t=3451|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=27 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727100253/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N_MNMZV9dTY&t=3451|url-status=live}}</ref> He made two starts and nine [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] appearances in the group stage of the league, where Al-Shorta finished 4th in Group 2 to qualify to the [[2015–16 Iraqi Premier League#Elite stage|Elite Stage]]. In the Elite Stage, the club finished in 7th position and Mohanad was used as a substitute for three of their six matches.

He spent the 2016–17 season on loan at Baghdad club [[Al-Kahrabaa FC|Al-Kahrabaa]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sportgram.net/المهاجم-الشاب-حسن-علي-يوقع-على-كشوفات-ا/|title=Al-Kahraba FC on a one-year loan deal from Al-Shorta|date=10 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314043824/http://www.sportgram.net/المهاجم-الشاب-حسن-علي-يوقع-على-كشوفات-ا/|archive-date=14 March 2018}}</ref> and finished as the top scorer for the club with 12 goals in 31 league matches,<ref name="MNT">{{NFT player}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Award Player of the Week |website=[[Facebook]] |url=https://www.facebook.com/alkahrabaa2020/posts/1317568351618884|date=8 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322203719/https://www.facebook.com/alkahrabaa2020/posts/1317568351618884|archive-date=22 March 2019}}</ref> including scoring four goals in the same match against [[Al-Karkh SC|Al-Karkh]] on 4 January. The club finished 13th in the league.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goalzz.com/?c=12547|title=Iraqi Premier League 2016/2017|publisher=Goalzz|access-date=28 April 2024|archive-date=28 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240428125848/https://www.goalzz.com/?c=12547|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Ali signed for [[Al-Naft SC|Al-Naft]] on loan, however Al-Shorta decided to terminate the loan shortly afterwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/mohammedalbndr/posts/pfbid0DmMaBdikp5kBktZguoeiGcYzwK2BLp81aP54sfT3Mz2MQsjD7NNdy9JKs1JRLgvxl|title=مهند علي وقع للنادي النفط|last=Abdullah|first=Mohammed|date=27 August 2017|language=ar|publisher=Al-Naft SC|access-date=28 April 2024|archive-date=28 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240428125848/https://www.facebook.com/mohammedalbndr/posts/pfbid0DmMaBdikp5kBktZguoeiGcYzwK2BLp81aP54sfT3Mz2MQsjD7NNdy9JKs1JRLgvxl|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2017–18 season====
Ali returned to Al-Shorta and renewed his contract in October 2017 for three years, taking the number 18 shirt. He scored his first two goals of the season against [[Naft Al-Junoob SC|Naft Al-Junoob]] in a 2–1 victory in January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iraqi League: Al Shurta - Nafit Al-Janob |url=https://www.fifa.com/live-scores/nationalleagues/nationalleague=iraq-iraqi-league-2000000099/matches/match=al-shurta-nafit-al-janob-300423236/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315003729/http://www.fifa.com/live-scores/nationalleagues/nationalleague=iraq-iraqi-league-2000000099/matches/match=al-shurta-nafit-al-janob-300423236/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 March 2018}}</ref> He continued to score regularly throughout the season, forming a partnership with fellow striker [[Alaa Abdul-Zahra]]. He scored his first [[Baghdad Derbies|Baghdad Derby]] goal against [[Al-Zawra'a SC|Al-Zawraa]] on 20 January and scoring in another Baghdad Derby against [[Al-Talaba SC|Al-Talaba]] on 30 January. He finished his season with the team with 16 goals and assisted 8 times in 32 appearances in the league. The team finished in 4th position.

====2018–19 season====
Ali began his season with his team with a new coach, [[Nebojša Jovović]], to exploit his speed as he also took on increasing defensive and creative duties. Mohanad scored his first goal and provided an assist in a 3–1 away win over Naft Al-Junoob on 21 October. He scored his second and third in a 3–0 win against [[Al-Sinaat Al-Kahrabaiya]]. On 7 November, Mohanad scored his fourth goal against former club Al-Kahrabaa.<ref>{{cite web|title=Left-foot shot that has torn the old net|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ev0DLoqeH4g|date=7 November 2018|access-date=26 October 2020|archive-date=22 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022122337/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ev0DLoqeH4g|url-status=live}}</ref> His fifth and sixth goal with his team came on 24 November including an impressive solo effort,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oLboQ6BxlwY&t=255|title=Great goal against Naft Maysan|website=[[YouTube]]|date=24 November 2018|access-date=16 July 2019|archive-date=22 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022122336/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oLboQ6BxlwY&t=255|url-status=live}}</ref> and he scored another extraordinary goal against [[Al-Naft]] on 4 March 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Juve, altro gol straordinario dell'obiettivo Mohanad Ali|url=https://video.gazzetta.it/juve-altro-gol-straordinario-obiettivo-mohanad-ali/8fbbcacc-3ff2-11e9-bc8e-2d2b2188e029|publisher=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|date=6 March 2019|language=it|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329110950/https://video.gazzetta.it/juve-altro-gol-straordinario-obiettivo-mohanad-ali/8fbbcacc-3ff2-11e9-bc8e-2d2b2188e029|url-status=live}}</ref> Mohanad scored 20 goals and 10 assists in 31 games; he won league with the club.

His good form at club level saw him on the radar of many of European and Asian clubs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad Ali is close to representing German club next season|url=http://www.football-iq.net/2018/03/13/خاص-مهند-علي-على-ابواب-احد-الاندية-الا/|date=13 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315070537/http://www.football-iq.net/2018/03/13/خاص-مهند-علي-على-ابواب-احد-الاندية-الا/|archive-date=15 March 2018}}<br>{{cite web|title=GENÇ IRAKLI RADARA GİRDİ|url=https://www.yeniasir.com.tr/spor/2018/07/01/rota-yine-yasin|website=Yeniasir|date=1 July 2018|language=tr|access-date=4 July 2018|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053830/https://vidoomy-d.openx.net/v/1.0/av?auid=540805079&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yeniasir.com.tr%2Fspor%2F2018%2F07%2F01%2Frota-yine-yasin&cb=292215&vwd=400&vht=225&schain=1.0%2C1!vidoomy.com%2C62924%2C1%2C71721139683111057379258212315%2C%2C&gdpr=0&gdpr_consent=|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Mohanad Ali on the radar of Saudi clubs|url=https://arabia.eurosport.com/article/5293568-%D8%B5%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B9-%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82|publisher=arabia.eurosport.com|date=17 October 2018|access-date=21 October 2018|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053819/https://www.eurosport.com/geoblocking.shtml|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web |title=Portuguese club Santa Clara is interested in Mohanad |url=https://www.iq-pro.net/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%A7-%D9%83%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AA%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%80%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%85/ |date=21 October 2018 |access-date=22 October 2018 |archive-date=23 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023034733/https://www.iq-pro.net/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%A7-%D9%83%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AA%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%80%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%85/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After his successful [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] campaign with the national team, there were official offers made from Italian clubs [[Juventus FC|Juventus]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive {{!}} The official offer @juventus sent to Al-Shorta SC to buy Mohannad Ali on a permanent basis|url=https://twitter.com/IraqiProPlayers/status/1090720590342819841|date=30 January 2019|access-date=5 March 2019|archive-date=24 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324152749/https://twitter.com/iraqiproplayers/status/1090720590342819841|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Per la Juventus è già estate: Ali+Ndombele|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calciomercato/2019/01/31-52751503/per_la_juventus_gi_estate_ali_ndombele|first=Filippo|last=Cornacchia|publisher=[[Tuttosport]]|date=31 January 2019|language=it-IT|access-date=5 March 2019|archive-date=6 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306044138/http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calciomercato/2019/01/31-52751503/per_la_juventus_gi_estate_ali_ndombele|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], Czech club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]], Danish club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]], Belgian club [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Balal|first1=Hassanane|title=Exclusive: Leaked Documents Reveal Several Huge European Clubs Chasing Mohanad Ali Transfer|url=https://iraqfootball.me/2019/01/26/exclusive-leaked-documents-reveal-several-huge-european-clubs-chasing-mohanad-ali-transfer|website=IRAQ FOOTBALL|date=26 January 2019|access-date=30 January 2019|archive-date=31 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131093612/https://iraqfootball.me/2019/01/26/exclusive-leaked-documents-reveal-several-huge-european-clubs-chasing-mohanad-ali-transfer/|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web |title=The offers |url=https://twitter.com/mustafataha/status/1089550222295027717 |website=@mustafataha |language=tr |date=27 January 2019 |access-date=29 March 2019 |archive-date=26 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426231841/https://twitter.com/mustafataha/status/1089550222295027717 |url-status=live }}</ref> Turkish club [[Galatasaray S.K.|Galatasaray]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Clubs interested in Mohanad Ali|url=http://www.iraqfg.com/ar/%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/246.aspx|publisher=Iraqfpg.com|date=26 January 2019|access-date=28 January 2019|archive-date=21 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321210715/http://www.iraqfg.com/ar/%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/246.aspx|url-status=dead}}</ref> Greek club [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], Emirati club [[Al Ain FC|Al-Ain]] and Qatari club [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20190128052343/http://www.iraqfg.com/ar/آخر-الأخبار/246.aspx بالارقام.. مبالغ العروض الاحترافية المقدمة إلى نادي الشرطة لشراء "ميمي"]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rudaw.net/arabic/sports/300120192 |title=نادي الشرطة العراقي يرفض انتقال "ميمي" إلى يوفينتوس الإيطالي |access-date=16 May 2021 |archive-date=16 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516180632/https://www.rudaw.net/arabic/sports/300120192 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/Alsalihim/status/1090888124769669121 |title=العروض الفعلية التي وصلت لغرض شراء نجم هجوم العراق ولاعب الشرطة #مهند_علي نادي الدحيل القطري |access-date=16 May 2021 |archive-date=16 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516102550/https://twitter.com/Alsalihim/status/1090888124769669121 |url-status=live }}</ref> but Al-Shorta rejected the offers on 29 January 2019, meaning he would spend the rest of the season at Al-Shorta.<ref>{{cite web|title=Al-Shorta Statement|url=https://socceriraq.net/2019/01/29/al-shorta-statement-mohanad-ali-going-nowhere-despite-juventus-offer/|website=[[Soccer Iraq]]|date=29 January 2019|access-date=30 January 2019|archive-date=30 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130164244/https://socceriraq.net/2019/01/29/al-shorta-statement-mohanad-ali-going-nowhere-despite-juventus-offer/|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Christian Emile - Players Agent|url=http://iraqfg.com/ar/%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/301.aspx|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329150302/http://iraqfg.com/ar/%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/301.aspx|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|title=Behrooz Dezhbod - Players Agent|url=http://www.ikhnews.com/index.php?page=article&id=183302|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329123743/http://www.ikhnews.com/index.php?page=article&id=183302|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Irak: le club de Mohanad Ali, jeune star de la Coupe d'Asie, dit avoir refusé une offre de la Juventus|url=https://www.beinsports.com/fr/serie-a/news/irak-le-club-de-mohanad-ali-jeune-star-de-la-/1099529|website=[[beIN SPORTS]]|language=fr|date=30 January 2019|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329112453/https://www.beinsports.com/fr/serie-a/news/irak-le-club-de-mohanad-ali-jeune-star-de-la-/1099529|url-status=live}}</ref>

The end of the winter transfer window did not stop clubs from expressing their interest in Mohanad, with Al-Shorta's vice-president Abdul-Wahab Al-Taei stating that offers had also now been made by English club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], Turkish clubs [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], [[Hatayspor]], [[Yeni Malatyaspor]] and [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]] who sent a delegation in April,<ref>{{cite web |title=A copy of a letter sent by İstanbul Başakşehir to Al-Shorta at the end of March |url=https://twitter.com/SoccerIraq/status/1125100328339279880 |publisher=[[Soccer Iraq]] |date=5 May 2019 |access-date=5 May 2019 |archive-date=14 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614065308/https://twitter.com/SoccerIraq/status/1125100328339279880 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.elsport.com/news/show/485452 |title=الشرطة العراقي يرفض الجلوس مع متصدر الدوري التركي بشأن "ميمي" |access-date=16 May 2021 |archive-date=16 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516102552/https://www.elsport.com/news/show/485452 |url-status=live }}</ref> Russian club [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat Grozny]], Qatari club [[Al-Wakrah SC|Al-Wakrah]] and an unnamed Japanese club. After months of speculation about which club Mohanad would sign with, he completed a move to Qatari side Al-Duhail in July who agreed to pay an undisclosed fee.

===Al-Duhail===
{{quote box|width=30%|align=right|quote="We contracted with Mohanad because we know his great abilities and we saw him with his national team and today he proved this, and he suffered continuous pressure from Doha and from outside Doha but he had great abilities and everyone saw his special goal today."|salign=left|source=– Portuguese coach [[Rui Faria]].<ref>[https://duhailsc.com/en/football/news/15149 "Rui Faria commenting on Mohanad"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329113033/https://duhailsc.com/en/football/news/15149 |date=29 March 2020 }}.</ref>}} On 15 July 2019, he transferred to Qatari side [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] on a five-year contract,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mohsen|first1=Mohamed|title=Al Duhail Includes The Iraqi Talent Mohanad Ali|url=https://www.duhailsc.qa/en/football/news/14703|website=Al Duhail SC|language=en-gb|date=15 July 2019|access-date=16 July 2019|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053823/https://www.duhailsc.qa/news/football/|url-status=live}}</ref> for a reported fee of $1.2 million. Mohanad made his debut for Al Duhail in the [[2019 AFC Champions League knockout stage#R16 West 3.1|AFC Champions League]] against [[Al Sadd SC|Al Sadd]] on 6 August, coming on as a second-half substitute. He scored his first goal with a solo effort after dribbling past [[Kara Mbodji]] and [[George Kwasi Semakor|George Kwasi]] in the 89th minute on 3 October,<ref>{{cite web |title=Al Duhail 2–1 Al Sailiya {{!}} QSL 2019–20 |website=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7-BKbMqpQiY&t=124 |access-date=30 August 2020 |archive-date=22 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022122337/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7-BKbMqpQiY&t=124 |url-status=live }}</ref> coming on as a substitute in the 71st minute, in a 2–1 home win against [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Plus |first1=Doha Stadium |title=Mohanad Ali goal helps Al Duhail beat Al Sailiya |url=http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/contentpage.aspx?article=Mohanad-Ali-goal-helps-Al-Duhail-beat-Al-Sailiya |date=3 October 2019 |access-date=12 October 2019 |archive-date=3 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203155726/http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/contentpage.aspx?article=Mohanad-Ali-goal-helps-Al-Duhail-beat-Al-Sailiya |url-status=dead }}</ref>

====Portimonense (loan)====
On 30 January 2020, he was sent on loan to [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]] for the rest of the [[2019–20 Primeira Liga|2019–20 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohanad Ali emprestado com opção de compra |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/portimonense/detalhe/mohanad-ali-emprestado-com-opcao-de-compra |website=www.record.pt |language=pt-PT |access-date=3 February 2020 |archive-date=3 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203161845/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/portimonense/detalhe/mohanad-ali-emprestado-com-opcao-de-compra |url-status=live }}</ref> Nineteen days later, Mohanad joined the team.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Informação |first1=Sul |title=Mohanad Ali faz primeiro treino pelo Portimonense e até já poderá ir ao Dragão |url=https://www.sulinformacao.pt/2020/02/mohanad-ali-faz-primeiro-treino-pelo-portimonense-e-ate-ja-podera-ir-ao-dragao/ |website=Sul Informação |language=pt-PT |date=17 February 2020 |access-date=30 August 2020 |archive-date=26 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026013753/https://www.sulinformacao.pt/2020/02/mohanad-ali-faz-primeiro-treino-pelo-portimonense-e-ate-ja-podera-ir-ao-dragao/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He made a debut five days later, coming on as a late substitute for [[Bruno Tabata]] in a 0–1 away loss against [[FC Porto|Porto]].

====Al-Sailiya (loan)====
On 29 August 2020, he was loaned to [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mohanad joined Al Sailiya on loan from Al Duhail|url=https://www.facebook.com/Alsailiyasportclub/photos/a.139756029494171/1990188857784203|date=29 August 2020|access-date=30 August 2020|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053845/https://www.facebook.com/Alsailiyasportclub/photos/a.139756029494171/1990188857784203|url-status=live}}</ref> Mohanad scored on his debut in a 1–1 draw against [[Al-Rayyan SC|Al-Rayyan]] on 3 September.<ref>{{cite web |title=QNB Stars League Week 1 - Al Sailiya 1 Al Rayyan 1 |url=https://www.qsl.qa/en/news/qnb-stars-league-week-1-al-sailiya-1-al-rayyan-1 |publisher=QSL |language=en |date=3 September 2020}}</ref> Mohanad helped Al-Sailiya win the [[Qatari Stars Cup]] for the first major honour in the club's history, scoring a goal in the final.<ref>{{cite web|title=Al Sailiya beat Al Rayyan to clinch Ooredoo Cup|url=https://www.gulf-times.com/story/687499/Al-Sailiya-beat-Al-Rayyan-to-clinch-Ooredoo-Cup|publisher=[[Gulf Times]]|language=ar|date=26 March 2021|access-date=14 May 2021|archive-date=14 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514130930/https://www.gulf-times.com/story/687499/Al-Sailiya-beat-Al-Rayyan-to-clinch-Ooredoo-Cup|url-status=live}}</ref> He also played the first three matches of Al-Sailiya's [[QFA Cup]]-winning campaign before suffering a head injury that kept him out of the semi-final and final. Mohanad played 27 games and scored 12 goals and had 3 assists in all competitions.

====Aris Thessaloniki (loan)====
On 31 August 2021, Ali was loaned to [[Super League Greece]] side [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris Thessaloniki F.C]]. in the form of a one-year loan and with a purchase option from Al-Duhail.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Team|first=Onsports|date=2021-09-01|title=Άρης: "Χτύπησε" με Μοχανάντ Άλι στο 90'!|url=https://www.onsports.gr/podosfairo/superleague/story/742277/aris-xtypise-me-ali-sto-90|access-date=2021-08-31|website=Onsports.gr|language=el|archive-date=31 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831214105/https://www.onsports.gr/podosfairo/superleague/story/742277/aris-xtypise-me-ali-sto-90|url-status=live}}</ref> However, after only a few games, Ali damaged his [[cruciate ligaments]], causing him to be sidelined for at least 6 months, to not only miss the majority of the season, but also miss the rest of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|World Cup qualifiers]] with the [[Iraq|Iraq national team]].

===Return to Al-Shorta===
In September 2023, Ali returned to Iraq to join his former club Al-Shorta.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.alkhaleej.ae/2023-09-26/%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9 |title="ميمي" يعود إلى الشرطة العراقي |website=alkhaleej.ae |language=ar |date=26 September 2023 |access-date=7 June 2024 |archive-date=16 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231016203044/https://www.alkhaleej.ae/2023-09-26/%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9 |url-status=live }}</ref>

== International career ==

===Youth===
Ali made his debut for Iraq's Under-14s in 2013 at the age of just 13. He was the joint-top scorer at the [[Football at the 2013 Asian Youth Games#Goalscorers|2013 Asian Youth Games]] with six goals in [[Nanjing]] in August 2013, where the Iraq beat Singapore,<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohanad (1st L) jumps for the ball during the men's football match against Kuwait at the 2nd Asian Youth Games|url=http://ocasia.org/AdminPanel/UploadFiles/Images-OCA/Football-Nanjing-2013_51163445013797.jpg|website=ocasia.org|date=17 August 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727154732/http://ocasia.org/AdminPanel/UploadFiles/Images-OCA/Football-Nanjing-2013_51163445013797.jpg|archive-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> Kuwait and Thailand in the quarterfinals before they lost to Iran in the semis and the third-place playoff on penalties to North Korea.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad against South Korea, Asian Youth Games|website=[[Facebook]]|url=https://www.facebook.com/Nanjing2013AsianYouthGames/photos/189784941193017/190382824466562|date=15 August 2013|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=3 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403075529/https://www.facebook.com/Nanjing2013AsianYouthGames/photos/189784941193017/190382824466562|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Hurra" /> In the first ever edition of the AFC U-14 Championship in 2014 in Iran,<ref name="Championship" >{{cite web|title=Iraq on AFC U-14 Championship victory|url=http://www.ffiri.ir/news/detail/تیم-ملی-عراق-قهرمان-مسابقات-فوتبال-زیر14-سال-آسیا-شد---عکس/116955/news.aspx |publisher=ffiri.ir|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608163818/http://www.ffiri.ir/news/detail/تیم-ملی-عراق-قهرمان-مسابقات-فوتبال-زیر14-سال-آسیا-شد---عکس/116955/news.aspx|language=fa|archive-date=8 June 2018}}</ref> Mohanad won the top-scorer award with six goals<ref name="Mohanad">{{cite web |title=Prolific Kadhim claims U-14 top scorer honour|url=http://www.the-afc.com/about-afc/news/prolific-kadhim-claims-u-14-top-scorer-honour-8270|publisher=AFC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604145910/http://www.the-afc.com/about-afc/news/prolific-kadhim-claims-u-14-top-scorer-honour-8270|archive-date=4 June 2018}}</ref> and his team won the cup.<ref name="AFC U14">{{cite web |title=Youtube – AFC U14 Championship Iran 2014 – FINAL |website=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ae_OsED2Pc0 |date=21 August 2014 |access-date=4 June 2018 |archive-date=23 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323103529/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ae_OsED2Pc0 |url-status=live }}<br>{{cite web|title=Shaikh Salman congratulates Iraq on AFC U-14 Championship victory|url=http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-u-14-championship/latest/news/shaikh-salman-congratulates-iraq-on-afc-u-14-championship-victory-8273|publisher=AFC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604143901/http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-u-14-championship/latest/news/shaikh-salman-congratulates-iraq-on-afc-u-14-championship-victory-8273|archive-date=4 June 2018}}</ref> In the [[2015 WAFF U-16 Championship]], Mohanad won the top scorer award with five goals and his team won the championship.<ref name="U-16">{{cite web|title=5th WAFF U-16 Championship 2015|url=http://www.the-waff.com/waff-news/العراق-بطلاً-للنسخة-الخامسة-للناشئين-960/|publisher=WAFF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224080619/http://www.the-waff.com/waff-news/العراق-بطلاً-للنسخة-الخامسة-للناشئين-960/|archive-date=24 December 2018|access-date=16 October 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Results of Iraq in 2015|url=http://niiiis.com/r2015.html|website=NIIIIS.com|access-date=23 December 2018|archive-date=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830234251/http://niiiis.com/r2015.html|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=2015 WAFF U-16 Championship|url=http://www.almadenahnews.com/article/400553|website=almadenahnews.com|date=6 August 2015|access-date=31 December 2018|archive-date=1 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190101002839/http://www.almadenahnews.com/article/400553|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="GU16">{{cite web|title=Video1 WAFF U-16 Championship 2015|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a8OunreVjdI&t=88|date=29 July 2015|access-date=14 January 2019|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053850/https://accounts.google.com/v3/signin/identifier?continue=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fsignin%3Faction_handle_signin%3Dtrue%26app%3Ddesktop%26hl%3Den%26next%3D%252Fsignin_passive%26feature%3Dpassive&hl=en&ifkv=AS5LTATb_9-Kia5C-JUuaet9jIy2qBeoB07gohIyD3QM_v0spovMsRYJACzBQs4I476lBnCq-6odgA&passive=true&service=youtube&uilel=3&flowName=GlifWebSignIn&flowEntry=ServiceLogin&dsh=S-584931594%3A1717738730716548&ddm=0|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Video2 WAFF U-16 Championship 2015|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eCEg2rNtzqo&t=108|date=2 August 2015|access-date=14 January 2019|archive-date=22 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322144948/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eCEg2rNtzqo&t=108|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Video3 WAFF U-16 Championship 2015|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhvTtyPvu3w|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=23 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023042043/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhvTtyPvu3w&gl=US&hl=en|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Video4 WAFF U-16 Championship 2015|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4D2C91aUBX8&t=160|date=6 August 2015|access-date=14 January 2019|archive-date=7 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607053928/https://accounts.google.com/v3/signin/identifier?continue=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fsignin%3Faction_handle_signin%3Dtrue%26app%3Ddesktop%26hl%3Den%26next%3D%252Fsignin_passive%26feature%3Dpassive&hl=en&ifkv=AS5LTAT7uSI36fUKnLU4Q8ekKVF-EMWwS7IGmYX38PIWL3Ah5_czmyXzdV0p1jula28EJKzblFR_vw&