===Senior===
[[File:Iran Iraq Football teams 2.jpg|thumb|left|Mohanad playing for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].]] He played his first match for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] in a friendly against [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]] on 17 December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=First match unofficial friendly against UAE|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_v9LjDgXYBk|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=23 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023042044/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_v9LjDgXYBk&gl=US&hl=en|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Call-up by Basim Qasim former manager|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yrt_NnyaBIs|date=19 February 2019|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=23 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023042044/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yrt_NnyaBIs&gl=US&hl=en|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored for Iraq in an unofficial friendly game against [[Iraqi Premier League]] club [[Naft Al-Junoob SC|Naft Al-Junoob]] on 24 February 2018.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=967470366133309440|user=SoccerIraq|title=📸 #Iraq played out a 1–1 draw in a friendly today against #IPL side Naft Al-Janoob. Mohanad Ali scored the Lions' g…<!-- full text of tweet that Twitter returned to the bot (excluding links) added by TweetCiteBot. This may be better truncated or may need expanding (TW limits responses to 140 characters) or case changes. --> |date=24 February 2018}}</ref> His first and second international goals for Iraq were in a friendly match against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] on 28 February 2018.<ref name="MNT"/>

He played against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] on 11 October 2018,<ref>{{cite web|title=¿Quién es Mohanad Ali, la joya de Irak?|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-internacional/mohanad-ali-joya-futbolista-irak-amistoso-argentina_0_2103389731.html|publisher=[[Olé (sports newspaper)|Olé]]|date=9 October 2018|language=es|access-date=17 October 2018|archive-date=10 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181010125820/https://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-internacional/mohanad-ali-joya-futbolista-irak-amistoso-argentina_0_2103389731.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> coming on as a second-half substitute.<ref name="MohanadVsDybala">{{cite web|title=Paulo Dybala vs Mohanad Ali|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EELnvpD1YiA&t=4850|date=11 October 2018|access-date=9 December 2018|archive-date=23 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323103541/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EELnvpD1YiA&t=4850|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Ramiro Funes Mori vs Mohanad Ali|website=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EELnvpD1YiA&t=3830|access-date=31 December 2018|archive-date=23 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323053107/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EELnvpD1YiA&t=3830|url-status=live}}</ref> He was nominated by the [[Asian Football Confederation]] (AFC) as one of the top young talents;<ref name="YSAFC">{{cite web|title=10 of the Best: Young Stars|url=http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/news/10-of-the-best-young-stars|publisher=AFC|date=14 December 2018|access-date=24 December 2018|archive-date=25 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225031116/http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/news/10-of-the-best-young-stars|url-status=live}}</ref> he was described as the youngest player who has the potential to changing the shape of the game before [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref name="it" />

He scored his seventh goal against [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]] on 8 January 2019,<ref>{{cite web |title=seventh goal against Vietnam |website=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iz_XkZ5Pc-A&t=35 |access-date=5 March 2019 |archive-date=22 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322144945/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iz_XkZ5Pc-A&t=35 |url-status=live }}<br>{{cite web |title=AFC Asian Cup 2019 Match Day 1: The Top 10 |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-asian-cup/1015789/afc-asian-cup-2019-match-day-1-the-top-10/ |access-date=14 January 2019 |archive-date=29 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329123811/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-asian-cup/1015789/afc-asian-cup-2019-match-day-1-the-top-10/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> and his eighth against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]] on 12 January 2019,<ref>{{cite web|title=GREAT GROUP STAGE GOALS: MOHANAD ALI V YEMEN|url=http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/videos/great-group-stage-goals-mohanad-ali-v-yemen|access-date=29 March 2019|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329110951/http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/videos/great-group-stage-goals-mohanad-ali-v-yemen|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web |title=Vote for your best player of UAE 2019 Group Stage! |url=http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/news/vote-for-your-best-player-of-uae-2019-group-stage |publisher=AFC |access-date=30 January 2019 |archive-date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130221018/http://www.the-afc.com/asiancup/news/vote-for-your-best-player-of-uae-2019-group-stage |url-status=live }}<br>{{cite web|title=The best U-21 players at the tournament|url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-asian-cup/1029494/afc-asian-cup-2019-the-best-u-21-players-at-the-tournament/|publisher=FOX Sports Asia|date=26 January 2019|access-date=30 January 2019|archive-date=30 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130221427/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-asian-cup/1029494/afc-asian-cup-2019-the-best-u-21-players-at-the-tournament/|url-status=dead}}</ref> followed by a goal against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] to help Iraq win the [[2019 International Friendship Championship]]. Mohanad went on to score five more goals by the end of 2019. After his performance at the 2019 AFC Asian Cup and [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]], he was voted the 2019 West Asian Footballer of the Year<ref>{{cite web |title=خيار الجماهير لأبرز لاعب في غرب آسيا 2019 |url=https://ar.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-champions-league/latest/news/west-asia-most-impressive-players-2019 |website=ar.the-afc.com |language=ar-SA |access-date=24 January 2020 |archive-date=29 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229121152/https://ar.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-champions-league/latest/news/west-asia-most-impressive-players-2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and was also included in Chinese newspaper ''[[Titan Sports (newspaper)|Titan Sports]]'' "[[Best Footballer in Asia 2019]]", which listed 26 of best footballers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://resource.ttplus.cn/publish/app/data/2020/01/03/294864/share1.html|title=【2019亚洲金球奖】26人完全排名+全球51位评委名单|work=Titan Sports|date=3 January 2020|language=zh|access-date=24 January 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329124959/https://resource.ttplus.cn/publish/app/data/2020/01/03/294864/share1.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Style of play==
{{Quote box|width=25%|align=right|quoted=1|quote=“We always trust Mohanad. He has good feet, he can connect powerfully with headers and he is very clever in the box."|salign=left|source=– Iraq youth coach Saad Hashim speaking on Mohanad.<ref name="Mohanad"/>}}
Ali is talented player with good technique and close control, who is an adept header of the ball, and who has an ability to score impressive goals, in the air or with either foot, courtesy of his shooting ability and positional sense. He is physically strong, and is gifted with [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, anticipation, and confidence in going at opponents with numerical superiority. He is also known for his speed, and his ability beat defenders with sudden turns, as well as his vision, which gave him the ability to link-up with and provide assists for teammates.<ref name="it" /><ref name="Hurra"/><ref name="YSAFC"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Los cinco jóvenes a seguir en la Copa Asia 2019|url=https://as.com/futbol/2019/01/03/internacional/1546538476_797754.html|first=Álex|last=de Llano|publisher=[[Diario AS|AS]]|language=es|date=3 January 2019|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=15 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240215052516/https://as.com/futbol/2019/01/03/internacional/1546538476_797754.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=La oferta irrisoria de la Juventus por Mohanad Ali, la joven promesa de Irak|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2215738-la-oferta-irrisoria-hizo-juventus-mohanad-ali|publisher=[[La Nación]]|language=es|access-date=5 March 2019|archive-date=3 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203172037/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2215738-la-oferta-irrisoria-hizo-juventus-mohanad-ali|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Ali is a [[Shammar tribe|Shammari]] [[Shia Islam in Iraq|Shiite]] born in [[Baghdad]]. The former international striker [[Ali Salah Hashim|Ali Salah]] is one of his cousins.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohanad is the cousin of Ali Salah |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BDh6KLryvJE/ |access-date=7 January 2019 |archive-date=12 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112094155/https://www.instagram.com/p/BDh6KLryvJE/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Mohanad played under the name of his brother Hassan Ali during the 2015–16 and 2016–17 seasons due to an error in his passport.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hassan Ali Kadhim profile with photo of Mohanad Ali|url=http://www.kooora.com/?player=102811&mode=|publisher=www.kooora.com|access-date=13 January 2019|archive-date=21 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321210712/http://www.kooora.com/?player=102811&mode=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mohanad Ali: I am not Hassan and this is the story of my personal details|url=http://www.football-iq.net/2017/04/04/%D9%85%D9%87%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7-%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%87%D8%B0%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B5%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D8%A7/|publisher=Football-IQ|date=4 April 2017|access-date=15 January 2019|archive-date=16 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116060043/http://www.football-iq.net/2017/04/04/%D9%85%D9%87%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7-%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%87%D8%B0%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B5%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D8%A7/|url-status=live}}</ref> An Iraqi court ruling in 2017 allowed him to obtain a corrected passport,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=The Iraqi striker with two names – free to play for Iraq at the Gulf Cup|url=https://ahdaaf.me/2017/12/12/the-iraqi-striker-with-two-names-free-to-play-for-iraq-at-the-gulf-cup/|publisher=Ahdaafme|date=12 December 2017|access-date=19 December 2017|archive-date=22 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222051632/https://ahdaaf.me/2017/12/12/the-iraqi-striker-with-two-names-free-to-play-for-iraq-at-the-gulf-cup/|url-status=usurped}}</ref> thus enabling him to represent Iraq again.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Iraqi court's ruling allows a player to return to the national team after being deprived internationally|url=http://www.football-iq.net/2017/12/11/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86/|publisher=Football-IQ|date=11 December 2017|access-date=26 March 2021|archive-date=29 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329150259/http://www.football-iq.net/2017/12/11/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Al-Nasser|first1=Falah|title=What is it Mohanad or Hassan|url=http://newsabah.com/newspaper/61585|publisher=newsabah.com|date=21 September 2015|access-date=13 January 2019|archive-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042354/http://newsabah.com/newspaper/61585|url-status=dead}}</ref> In late September 2020 he tested positive for [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1309455524665139202|user=alkasschannel|title=الفحوصات الطبية تثبت إصابة العراقي #مهند_علي محترف نادي #السيلية بفيروس #كورونا<!-- full text of tweet that Twitter returned to the bot (excluding links) added by TweetCiteBot. This may be better truncated or may need expanding (TW limits responses to 140 characters) or case changes. --> |date=25 September 2020}}</ref>

